Our Client, a large federal government Agency is seeking a Business Intelligence Analyst to join their Data and Analytics Branch which supports the Agency by providing high quality data and reporting, and translating insights into measurable business performance improvements. It focuses on delivering data and reporting while building data literacy capability across the branch and regions.


The position is a team leadership position within the Agency and will have delegated authority and responsibility to resolve issues and risks across a range of activities. The role is required to provide leadership, control, planning, resource management, performance management and decision making for the Team Membership within the work area.


Responsibilities of the role include but are not limited to:
Translating subject-matter expert and stakeholder discussions into data and reporting products;
Translating key data insights into value adding products;
Articulating complex information into clear and straightforward messages and providing specialist advice that key stakeholders with varied levels of data literacy can consume;
Designing and building reports, dashboards and data products, support business processes, completing complex tasks and delivering business insight;
Driving best practice across the Analytics Chapter to ensure consistent analytics methodology and approach, facilitating initiatives and contributing to business improvement strategies;
Building, developing and maintaining code base;
Mentoring and leading of junior analysts.

Essential criteria
Advanced programming expertise (eg. SAS and/or SQL);
Proven ability to extract and manipulate data whilst maintaining accuracy and consistency.

For a copy of the full job description, please reach out to Alison at the Recruitment Hive by clicking the Apply Now button or calling Alison on (02)6299 1006. Please note, applications close on the 29th of November at 11:00AM.

Job ID AC10209

Gain exposure to one of the key income areas of the business
Flexible / Hybrid working environment & collaborative team
Work for Australia's leading retail pharmacy network
About us:
At TerryWhite Chemists (TWC), we are dedicated to delivering frontline healthcare, ensuring every Australian has easy access to expert health advice and outstanding pharmaceutical care.
Our vision is to build a better future for Australian pharmacy, and we need passionate individuals like you to help us achieve this goal.
TWC is a subsidiary of the EBOS Group. With almost 5,000 employees in 109 locations across Australia, New Zealand, and Southeast Asia, EBOS Group is the largest and most diversified Australasian marketer, wholesaler and distributor of healthcare, medical and pharmaceutical products. It is also a leading marketer and distributor of recognised animal care brands.
EBOS Group is publicly listed on the New Zealand and Australian stock exchanges. 
The Role:
TWC is seeking an experienced and savvy Commercial Analyst to join their commercial finance team on a 12-month contract basis.
Based out of our Brisbane Support Centre in Milton, QLD and reporting directly to the Commercial & Data Services Manager, you will be responsible to collect and reconcile merchandise income. This position is vital to providing day to day financial advice and providing regular reporting to the cost centre owners within the Merchandise department on their financial position against budgets.
What’s exciting about this role is you are in the engine room of our support office. It’s a fast-paced environment in a critical position that has high stakeholder engagement. Outcomes of your work will be presented to the cost centres owners, General Managers, Chief Commercial Officer and the Executive General Manager each and every week therefore your ability to build strong working relationships, work collaboratively with diverse teams and communicate effectively at all levels will be key to success.
Applicants based in Melbourne will be considered.
What you will do:
Partner and actively engage the merchandise team on understanding and delivering on their financials;
Support, manage & report on the Merchandise budget and forecasting activity;
Complete variance analysis on actuals against budgets and forecast, providing commentary and recommending solutions to key stakeholders to support effective decision making;
Review and complete month end financial requirements for the Merchandise team and reconcile P&Ls;
Assist with the review of promotional activity to ensure that Sales Orders are raised correctly. 
What we are looking for:
Knowledge of the retail sector. Commercial experience within the pharmacy industry preferred but not essential;
Experience working within a Commercial Analyst or similar role;
Ability to apply commercial acumen to your analysis;
Exceptional organisational and time management skills;
Self-starter with the ability to grasp tasks and concepts quickly;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to organise and coordinate multiple stakeholders.
Benefits
At TWC we are committed to delivering exceptional healthcare services and fostering innovation in a dynamic marketplace. This is a unique opportunity to work in a company where you are valued, given the recognition you deserve and suitably rewarded for your hard work.
Other benefits include:
Employee Share Plan;
Company Paid Parental Leave;
Employee Assistance Program for Mental Health Wellbeing;
Staff Awards;
Employee Referral Program;
Health Insurance Discounts.
EBOS Group are committed to developing and creating an inclusive workplace that embraces and celebrates diversity and inclusion. We recognise that a diverse workplace improves our ability to attract, retain, motivate and develop talent, create an engaged workforce, deliver quality services to our customers and to support the growth of EBOS Group.
EBOS Group are an equal opportunity employer and encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities and cultures including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples.
How to apply
If you believe that you have the necessary attributes to succeed in this challenging and rewarding role, please click ‘APPLY’ now. 
Pre-employment checks may be required and will be discussed with the successful candidate.
We are unable to proceed with your application if your current visa restrictions preclude you from being able to perform the role in line with immigration laws.
No agency assistance required.

We are looking for an experienced Business Analyst to join our energy sector client’s Enterprise Data Group within their Digital Division. This role involves leveraging data to drive business decisions, and fostering innovation. Strong communication and stakeholder management skills are essential, along with technical knowledge of SAP S/4HANA to assist in transitioning data models and reports to SAP Rise.
 Responsibilities:
Liaise with employees and management to translate business requirements into detailed functional specifications, especially matching business processes with system requirements;
Reverse engineer reporting requirements from existing report specifications. Identify information sets, source data and business logic or calculations applied and then document reporting requirements;
Work with business stakeholders and data analysts to elicit requirements and translate into user stories;
Identify information sets, source data and business logic or calculations applied and then document requirements in the form of user stories;
Undertake testing activity to ensure data analysis functionality (including visualisations) correlate with specified business requirements;
Undertake functional testing activities related to the development and implementation of the platform;
Support project team/s to successfully deliver the project/s using contemporary tools and applications such as Jira and Confluence;
Ability to develop and deliver presentations that clearly articulate the issues and proposed solutions, in a dynamic / changing environment;
Create data visualisation mock-ups and reverse engineer requirements from existing solutions if required;
 Required skills and experience:
Demonstrated experience working as a Business Analyst on an Enterprise Intelligence / Data Platform.
Demonstrated ability in building effective relationships with business stakeholders and ICT service providers with the ability to negotiate outcomes in a complex environment
Demonstrated experience working on projects that provide corporate dashboard and reporting solutions to Business units and Executive level management teams
Competent in understanding SQL and embedded business rules
Technical understanding of existing SAP products (S4/HANNA; SAC)
Practical experience in project tools and applications such as JIRA, Confluence and SharePoint
Understanding of Project Delivery life cycle and Agile methodology
 The following are highly desirable:
Experience in authoring dashboards, reports and preparing presentations for senior audiences
Experience and knowledge of the energy industry with an understanding of potential future directions across the sector
Demonstrated experience working with regulated entities and an understanding of the compliance requirements, including reporting and provision of information to regulatory bodies
Competent in understanding Excel advanced functionality (as may be used by accountants and engineers)
 This role will be offered as an initial 6 month contract and is due to start asap.
 How to Apply
Please include your resume and contact details.
Contact Natalie at Data#3 on 0430 292 875 or natalie_keam@data3.com.au for any questions. If you do not meet the role criteria but are still interested in hearing about opportunities through Data#3, please also get in touch for more info on our other available positions!
Data#3 will request as part of the recruitment process reference checks and verification of your right to work in Australia. All final applicants for this position will be asked to consent to a police check.
Please note that applicants with criminal records will not automatically be excluded from the recruitment process. Each application will be considered on its merits and inherent requirements of the role.
